According media spokesperson for the Middelburg SAPS, Captain Khanyisile Zwane, the robbery took place at 02:30 this morning. The security guard on duty was approached by three armed men, who tied him up with shoelaces at gunpoint. The armed men had gained access to the store by breaking open a window as well as a door. The security had managed to untie himself and called his supervisor. Upon the policeâ€™s arrival, it was found that two safes had been broken into. According to Captain Zwane, the police could not yet ascertain what was held in the safes, but the guard fortunately escaped without injury.